# Jean-Claude

Jean-Claude is a local machine assistant.

The current version focuses on a modular core:

- chat with an LLM
- tool system with executable tools
- YAML-driven flow/state machine
- filesystem prompt pack (editable without code changes)

The first built-in tool is `bash.run`.

## Quickstart

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .
```

## Auth (OpenAI Codex OAuth)

```bash
jc auth login openai-codex
jc auth status openai-codex
jc auth logout openai-codex
```

## Chat

Interactive:

```bash
jc chat --provider openai-codex --model gpt-5.3-codex
```

One-shot:

```bash
jc chat --provider openai-codex --model gpt-5.3-codex --message "List files in your home directory"
```

Mock mode (offline testing):

```bash
jc chat --provider mock --message "List files in your home directory"
```

## Tools

List tools:

```bash
jc tools list
```

Show execution policy:

```bash
jc tools policy show
```

Default is strict allowlist.

Enable unrestricted mode (explicit opt-in):

```bash
jc tools policy set unrestricted --yes-i-understand
```

Switch back to safe default:

```bash
jc tools policy set allowlist
```

## Debug Logs

Use `--debug` on `chat` and `llm test` to inspect prompts, payloads, tool calls, and provider responses.

Debug logs are printed to stderr.

## Prompt Pack

Prompt/flow/tool definitions are external files in `prompts/`:

- `prompts/base/`
- `prompts/modes/`
- `prompts/tools/`
- `prompts/flows/`
- `prompts/schemas/`

Override location with:

- `JEAN_CLAUDE_PROMPTS_DIR`

## State Files

- auth: `~/.jean-claude/auth.json`
- tool settings: `~/.jean-claude/settings.json`

Override base state directory with:

- `JEAN_CLAUDE_STATE_DIR`
